cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AR, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification and sentiment analysis. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of transfer learning and network compression techniques for efficient on-device NLP applications. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is relevant as the paper mentions the use of CNN-DSA chips, which are commonly used in computer vision applications. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the NLP applications on mobile devices using domain-specific accelerator chips. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for NLP tasks.
